<%- include('partials/head') %>
<section class="helper-hero">
  <article class="panel helper-status-card">
    <div class="panel-head">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">GS Companion</p>
        <h2>Companion Status</h2>
      </div>
      <span class="status <%= helper.connected ? 'ready' : 'needs_review' %>"><%= helper.statusLabel %></span>
    </div>
    <div class="helper-detail-grid">
      <p class="row-line"><span>Device</span><strong><%= helper.device && helper.device.device_name ? helper.device.device_name : 'Not connected' %></strong></p>
      <p class="row-line"><span>Last heartbeat</span><strong><%= helper.lastHeartbeat ? new Date(helper.lastHeartbeat).toLocaleString() : 'Never' %></strong></p>
      <p class="row-line"><span>Helper version</span><strong><%= helper.helperVersion %></strong></p>
      <p class="row-line"><span>Current user</span><strong><%= user.globalName || user.username %></strong></p>
      <p class="row-line"><span>Connection token</span><strong><%= helper.tokenStatus %></strong></p>
    </div>
    <% if (!helper.connected) { %>
      <p class="notice">Install and run GS Account Manager Companion to open controlled Chrome with proxies and use assisted browser actions.</p>
    <% } %>
  </article>

  <article class="panel download-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Download</p>
    <h2>Download GS Account Manager Companion</h2>
    <div class="helper-detail-grid">
      <p class="row-line"><span>Latest version</span><strong><%= download.version %></strong></p>
      <p class="row-line"><span>Release date</span><strong><%= download.releaseDate %></strong></p>
      <p class="row-line"><span>File size</span><strong><%= download.fileSize || 'Not available' %></strong></p>
    </div>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="button primary" href="<%= download.windowsPath %>">Download for Windows</a>
      <% if (!download.available) { %><span class="tag">Coming soon</span><% } %>
    </div>
    <p class="muted">Install instructions will appear here when the Windows package is released. Only download the helper from GS Account Manager.</p>
    <p class="notice">Safety note: the helper keeps browser work on your PC and must not bypass CAPTCHA, Cloudflare, security checks, verification, or 2FA.</p>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="content-grid">
  <article class="panel">
    <div class="panel-head">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Pairing</p>
        <h2>Connect This Account</h2>
      </div>
      <form method="post" action="/local-helper/pairing-code">
        <input type="hidden" name="_csrf" value="<%= csrfToken %>">
        <button class="button">Generate Helper Pairing Code</button>
      </form>
    </div>
    <% if (pairingCode) { %>
      <div class="code-box">
        <span>Pairing code</span>
        <strong><%= pairingCode.code %></strong>
        <small>Expires <%= new Date(pairingCode.expiresAt).toLocaleString() %></small>
      </div>
    <% } else { %>
      <p class="muted">Generate a code when the helper asks you to connect. Codes expire after 10 minutes and are stored only as hashes server-side.</p>
    <% } %>
  </article>

  <article class="panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">Setup</p>
    <h2>Setup Instructions</h2>
    <ol class="helper-list">
      <li>Download GS Account Manager Companion.</li>
      <li>Install or unzip it.</li>
      <li>Open the helper on your PC.</li>
      <li>Sign in or connect it to your GS Account Manager account.</li>
      <li>Return to this page and confirm it shows Connected.</li>
      <li>Use Dashboard or Workflow to open Chrome with selected proxy.</li>
    </ol>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="content-grid">
  <article class="panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">Capabilities</p>
    <h2>What the Helper Does</h2>
    <ul class="helper-list">
      <li>Opens Chrome with selected proxy.</li>
      <li>Uses per-account browser profiles.</li>
      <li>Shows whether proxy or direct mode is used.</li>
      <li>Can receive user-click browser actions.</li>
      <li>Can copy/fill selected account values when clicked, later.</li>
      <li>Keeps local browser work on the user's PC.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <article class="panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">Boundaries</p>
    <h2>What the Helper Does Not Do</h2>
    <ul class="helper-list">
      <li>Does not bypass CAPTCHA.</li>
      <li>Does not bypass Cloudflare or security checks.</li>
      <li>Does not perform hidden background account actions.</li>
      <li>Does not run unattended mass actions.</li>
      <li>Does not submit sensitive forms unless explicitly designed later with user confirmation.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</section>

<section class="panel">
  <p class="eyebrow">Advanced</p>
  <h2>Helper Connection Design</h2>
  <p class="muted">Devices, commands, and pairing codes are scoped to your user account. Device tokens and pairing codes are stored only as hashes. The current web app does not send browser automation commands yet.</p>
  <div class="checklist-grid">
    <p class="row-line"><span>Pending commands</span><strong><%= helper.commandCounts.pending || 0 %></strong></p>
    <p class="row-line"><span>Running commands</span><strong><%= helper.commandCounts.running || 0 %></strong></p>
    <p class="row-line"><span>Completed commands</span><strong><%= helper.commandCounts.completed || 0 %></strong></p>
  </div>
</section>
<%- include('partials/foot') %>
